1 Reading CSV

1.1 From the web

  • 直接從網路上載入台北市竊盜案資料
  • df <- read.csv(url, fileEncoding = "big5")這行的意思是把上面那個url用read.csv()這個函式讀取。讀取的同時，由於一般EXCEL為中文編碼BIG5，所以該文件八成是該台北市政單位還用EXCEL在編資料，所以要跟程式碼講說，這個網址所指到的檔案編碼為BIG5。
    • fileEncoding = "big5"稱為read.csv()這個函式的**參數(parameter)。
library(httr)
url <- "http://data.taipei/opendata/datalist/datasetMeta/download?id=68785231-d6c5-47a1-b001-77eec70bec02&rid=34a4a431-f04d-474a-8e72-8d3f586db3df"
df <- read.csv(url, fileEncoding = "big5")

1.4 (Option) Geting a file back to local directory

  • 部分Mac電腦無法使用read.csv()從網路上取得資料又轉為data.frame，一個可行的辦法是先用GET(url, write_disk("data/tptheft.csv"))將其取回並命名為data/tptheft.csv，之後再用df <- read.csv("data/tptheft.csv", fileEncoding = "big5", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)直接讀取該檔案。
library(httr)
GET(url, write_disk("data/tptheft.csv", overwrite = TRUE))
## Response [https://data.taipei/opendata/datalist/datasetMeta/download?id=68785231-d6c5-47a1-b001-77eec70bec02&rid=34a4a431-f04d-474a-8e72-8d3f586db3df]
##   Date: 2019-09-22 10:28
##   Status: 200
##   Content-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8
##   Size: 158 kB
## <ON DISK>  /Users/jirlong/Dropbox/Programming/R/R4CSS/data/tptheft.csv
df <- read.csv("data/tptheft.csv", fileEncoding = "big5", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

3 Cleaning data

  • 目標：「發生時段」我打算取出前面的數字來代表時間就好，「發生地點」我打算只取出行政區名，其他地址不要。邏輯上，我要把那串字取出第x個字到第y個字，所以要用substr()這個函式，或者未來會教到的stringr::str_sub()函式。
  • 用?substr查詢其用法和意義。相當於getting sub string since x to y。
# Get substring of var "發生時段" and assign to a new time var
df$time <- substr(df$發生時段, 1, 2)

# Get substring of var "發生.現.地點" and assign to a new region var
df$region <- substr(df$發生.現.地點, 4, 5)

4 Pivot analysis: Counting and Summarizing

  • 我們要回答的第一個數據問題通常是，那XXX的案例有幾個？例如大安區有多少竊盜案？買超過10000元訂單的客戶有多少人？男生和女生會修程式課的個別有多少人？這稱為計數。

4.2 Counting by tapply()

  • Using length() as counting method
# tapply() one arbitrary var by var time with length() function
tapply(df$編號, df$time, length)
##  00  01  02  04  06  07  08  10  12  13  14  16  18  19  20  22 
##  30 167  61 175  42 232  44 384  59 254  60 281  61 250  55 281

tapply(df$編號, df$region, length)

5 Filtering data

df <- df[!df$time %in% c("00", "02", "06", "08", "12", "14" ,"18", "20"), ]
df <- df[!df$region %in% c("三重", "中和", "淡水", "板橋"), ]

8 Plotting

# mosaicplot() to plot 2-dim categorical vars.
mosaicplot(res_table)

# Add argument main (figure title)
mosaicplot(res_table, main="mosaic plot")

8.2 (Option) Self-defined color?

# Set up color by yourself.
colors <- c('#D0104C', '#DB4D6D', '#E83015',  '#F75C2F',
            '#E79460', '#E98B2A', '#9B6E23', '#F7C242',

mosaicplot(res_table, color=colors, border=0, off = 3,
           main="Theft rate of Taipei city (region by hour)")

10 (dplyr) on tp theft

# readr::guess_encoding("data/tp_theft.csv")
library(readr)
library(tidyverse)
## ── Attaching packages ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── tidyverse 1.2.1 ──
## ✔ ggplot2 3.1.0     ✔ purrr   0.2.5
## ✔ tibble  1.4.2     ✔ dplyr   0.7.8
## ✔ tidyr   0.8.2     ✔ stringr 1.3.1
## ✔ ggplot2 3.1.0     ✔ forcats 0.3.0
## ── Conflicts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── tidyverse_conflicts() ──
## ✖ dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()
## ✖ dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()
df <- read_csv("data/tp_theft.csv", locale = locale(encoding = "Big5")) %>% 
    select(id = 編號, 
           cat = 案類, 
           date = `發生(現)日期`, 
           time = `發生時段`, 
           location = `發生(現)地點`) %>% # glimpse()
    mutate(year = date %/% 10000) %>%
    mutate(month = date %/% 100 %% 100) %>%
    mutate(location = stringr::str_sub(location, 4, 6)) %>%
    # count(year) %>% View
    filter(year >= 104) %>%
    # count(time) %>% View
    filter(!time %in% c("00~02", "02~04", "06~08", "08~10", "12~14")) %>%
    # count(location) %>%
    filter(!location %in% c("中和市", "板橋市")) %>%
    count(time, location) %>%
    spread(location, n, fill=0) 
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   編號 = col_integer(),
##   案類 = col_character(),
##   `發生(現)日期` = col_integer(),
##   發生時段 = col_character(),
##   `發生(現)地點` = col_character()
## )
par(family=('STKaiti'))
row.names(df) <- df$time
df$time <- NULL
mosaicplot(df, color=colors, border=0, off = 3, main="Theft rate of Taipei city (region by hour)")
